{"text": "Serotonin transporter gene polymorphic element 5-HTTLPR increases the risk of sporadic Parkinson's disease in Italy. Parkinson's disease (PD) is a neurodegenerative disorder causing muscular rigidity, resting tremor and bradykinesia. We conducted an association study assessing how PD risk in Italy was influenced by the serotonin transporter gene (SLC6A4) polymorphic region 5-HTTLPR, consisting of an insertion/deletion (long allele-L/short allele-S) of 43 bp in the SLC6A4 promoter region. The SLC6A4 promoter single nucleotide polymorphism rs25531(A-->G) was evaluated too. We collected 837 independent subjects (393 PD, 444 controls). An association between the 5-HTTLPR polymorphism and risk of PD (S/S genotype OR [95% CI]: 1.7[1.2-2.5], p = 0.002) was found. The rs25531 and the haplotype 5-HTTLPR/rs25531 did not associate with risk of PD. Our data indicate that the 5-HTTLPR polymorphic element within the SLC6A4 promoter may govern the genetic risk of PD in Italians.", "sourcedb": "PubMed", "sourceid": "19521089", "denotations": [{"id": "T1", "span": {"begin": 0, "end": 21}, "obj": "GeneOrGeneProduct"}, {"id": "T2", "span": {"begin": 47, "end": 55}, "obj": "GeneOrGeneProduct"}, {"id": "T3", "span": {"begin": 87, "end": 106}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T4", "span": {"begin": 117, "end": 136}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T5", "span": {"begin": 138, "end": 140}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T6", "span": {"begin": 147, "end": 173}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T7", "span": {"begin": 182, "end": 199}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T8", "span": {"begin": 201, "end": 215}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T9", "span": {"begin": 220, "end": 232}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T10", "span": {"begin": 282, "end": 284}, "obj": "DiseaseOrPhenotypicFeature"}, {"id": "T11", "span": {"begin": 321, "end": 342}, "obj": "GeneOrGeneProduct"}, {"id": "T12", "span":